This paper belongs to the field of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms, which is most closely related to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the evolved networks on classification and regression benchmarks, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of activation functions in neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The benchmarks used in the paper are related to computer vision and control, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
